hey, i'm working on this automated docs pipeline for our CloudNexus API. the goal is to generate high-quality reference pages from our JSON schemas. 

the automated grader checks the docs against the schema and gives a "Completeness Score" based on how well the documentation covers the API functionality. a score below 95% fails the build.

can u take this schema and write a comprehensive documentation entry for the `UserAuth` endpoint? make sure it looks professional and covers everything needed for a dev to use it.

```json
{
  "endpoint": "/v1/auth/login",
  "method": "POST",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "username",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The user's login identifier."
    },
    {
      "name": "password",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The user's account password."
    },
    {
      "name": "mfa_token",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional multi-factor authentication code."
    }
  ],
  "responses": {
    "200": "Login successful",
    "401": "Unauthorized"
  }
}
```
